For example, you may occasionally see a function that returns a floating point literal (typically0.0, or sometimes1.0). In such cases, it is safe to do a direct comparison against the same literal value of the same type:if (someFcn() == 0.0) // okay if someFcn() returns 0.0 as a literal only
