The most common method of doing floating point equality involves using a function that looks to see if two numbers arealmostthe same. If they are “close enough”, then we call them equal. The value used to represent “close enough” is traditionally calledepsilon. Epsilon is generally defined as a small positive number (e.g. 0.00000001, sometimes written 1e-8).New developers often try to write their own “close enough” function like this:#include <cmath> // for std::abs()

